        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Washington&#44; D. C.<lb/>
                September 3d 1880.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. and dear friend.<lb/></p>
            <p>Through<lb/> the mercy of Almighty<lb/> God&#44; I am once more per&#45;<lb/>mitted to address you<lb/> on the Eve of a New Year&#44;<lb/> and to offer the sincere<lb/> prayer that health and<lb/> happiness may be the<lb/> lot of you and yours&#44;<lb/> for many years to come&#44;<lb/> in which I can most<lb/> cordially joined by Every<lb/> member of my family.<lb/></p>
            <p>I am sure you will<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>be pleased to know that<lb/> Mrs. Solomons&#39; health is<lb/> very much better&#44; and<lb/> that we are encouraged<lb/> to believe she will entirely recover.<lb/></p>
            <p>With assurances of<lb/> profound respect&#44;<lb/>
                I am&#44;<lb/>
                Yours Truly<lb/>
                A. S. Solomons<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S  Morais.<lb/>
                Philadelphia.<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
